column2: STUDY INFORMATION SHEET
Study of Social Perception

Kerri L. Johnson and associates from the Department of Psychology at the University of California, Los Angeles are conducting a research study. You were selected as a possible participant in this study because you are 18 years or older.  Your participation in this research study is completely voluntary.
WHY IS THIS STUDY BEING DONE?

Research designs often require that the full intent of a study is not explained prior to participation. Although we will describe the general nature of the tasks that you will be asked to perform, our full intent will not be explained to you until after the completion of the study.  At that time, we will provide you with a full debriefing which will include an explanation of the hypothesis that was tested and other relevant background information pertaining to the study.  You will also be given an opportunity to leave comments about the hypothesis and procedures of the study.
This research is designed to improve our understanding of the factors that contribute to social judgments.  We are interested in the process and consequences of certain aspects of social perception.
WHAT WILL HAPPEN IF I TAKE PART IN THIS RESEARCH STUDY?
If you volunteer to participate in this study, you will be asked to do the following:

column1: -      Complete several questionnaires about your background and personality. -      Provide several judgments about other people based on minimal information such as a picture/video of their face or body.

column2: All of these activities will take place online, so you can complete them in your own time and at the location of your choice.  Furthermore, your responses will remain completely confidential, and you may choose not to answer any questions that make you uncomfortable without receiving any penalty or affecting your participation in any way.
HOW LONG WILL I BE IN THE RESEARCH STUDY?
Participation in the study will take a total of about 20 minutes.
ARE THERE ANY RISKS OR DISCOMFORTS THAT I CAN EXPECT FROM THIS STUDY?

Some of the questions posed in the questionnaires ask for information about your self-views and your judgments of other people.  Revealing this information may make some people feel uncomfortable.  Please be aware that you may skip any items you do not wish to answer for any reason and without penalty.
ARE THERE ANY BENEFITS IF I PARTICIPATE?

You will not directly benefit from your participation in this research.  However, the results of the research may create an advancement of knowledge that will help us to better understand what determines people’s judgments of others.
WILL I BE PAID FOR MY PARTICIPATION?
You will receive $3.00 in exchange for your participation.
HOW WILL INFORMATION ABOUT ME AND MY PARTICIPATION BE KEPT CONFIDENTIAL?

No information that is obtained during this study will be identified with you. While we want you to share your real feelings and your real experiences during the survey, we will not ask that you provide your name or other identifying information.
WHAT ARE MY RIGHTS IF I TAKE PART IN THIS STUDY?

Taking part in this study is your choice. You can choose whether or not you want to participate. Whatever decision you make, there will be no penalty to you and you will not lose any of your regular benefits.

column1: -      You have a right to have all of your questions answered before deciding whether to take part.
-      If you decide to take part, you can leave the study at anytime.
-      You may refuse to answer any questions you don’t want to answer and still remain in the study.

column2: WHO CAN I CONTACT IF I HAVE QUESTIONS ABOUT THIS STUDY?
The Research Team:
You may contact Dr. Kerri Johnson at socomlab@gmail.com with any questions or concerns about the research or your participation in this study.
UCLA Office of the Human Research Protection Program (OHRPP):
